node.text:
Hey friends! Sooo I removed my instagram and FB from my phone. 

Here’s why. The privacy you don’t have from these platforms is terrible. 
They have access to EVERYTHING.... I’ll let you do your own research if this concerns you. 

Also I just wanted to spend less time on them and be more present with my life and it’s working out great!!! 

I find it crazy how addicting it can be. Do your fingers just magnet to these platforms even when you may not want them to?! Mine sure do...

Also, I get disappointed when I’m with friends or family and they just zone out and disappear from hanging out with us into online social World. They are just gone... 

Anyway It’s been amazing!!! I wish I did it sooner!!! So I had to share this idea with y’all so you to may experience the freedom and goodness of just owning your time and life! 
Lots of ❤️✌🏽

node.title: I removed my social off my phone 🤗❌📱

node.text:
Friends of Bethany is now the Beautifully Flawed Foundation! 🎉

As our foundation has grown over the years, we felt a passion to widen the platform for others to shine their stories of hope and impact the world around them. I’m excited to see the growth of this non profit and continue to support and be apart of the amazing retreats we’ve been doing for years now!!!

Now known as the Beautifully Flawed Foundation, more opportunities are being created to partner with and highlight the many incredible people impacted by our programs. The name may have changed but not the focus: with the mission of offering hope to those impacted by the brokenness of his world to overcome through Jesus Christ.

Check out @beautifullyflawed_foundation to learn more, or head to their website beautifullyflawedfoundation.com! #friendsofbethany #beautifullyflawedfoundation

node.text:
Merry Christmas season!!! I hope you and your loved ones are hanging in there!

Adam and I want to share life empowerment and encourage YOU in a more intentional way. This has sure been a tough year, and it got me thinking about the difficult times of my life and how it has been my community and faith that uplift and encourage me to keep going. We want to do the same for you so we just launched a new private Facebook group that will be a place of encouragement and intentional living to empower you and create a community of positivity!

We’ll be diving deep into Unstoppable Living by digging into some of the tough and essential topics of life, encouraging you in the progress of your goals, and sharing in monthly live Q&As with Adam and me. This is a motivating and uplifting community to empower and support YOU
💥

Our first live Q&A will be this Wednesday, December 16th, so join TODAY to participate! Join the group here: bit.ly/UnstoppableLiving #linkinbio

Dips & sauces make food so fun and delicious, so that is where I often start in the kitchen! This is the first time I’ve made this green onion dip with no recipe. That’s my style, I like to wing it. And I’ll show you how! Green onions are kinda like that ‘what do I do with you’ food for me but I enjoyed them in this creamy dip! “Sometimes the most productive thing you can do is stepping back and enjoying your time.” - #KateMerrick

Life can be so full on with noise, news, social media, texts, emails and it’s all nonstop and can be  overwhelming and steal from our peace and happiness! 
So how can we deal?! 

I truly believe that living out life being present will result in good & beautiful changes, deeper connections, more fun, and increased peace and gratitude! I recently sat down with Kate Merrick, author of the book “Here and Now”, to talk about how we can be more present in our lives, especially in this year 2020. I hope you find some words of encouragement here and if the chaos is getting to you set boundaries, slow down and be present!!! You won’t regret it ❤️❤️❤️

Watch our full conversation here: https://bit.ly/383abwt #linkinbio

node.text: Last month I had a rad conversation with super talented musical artist, father, and husband @lecrae. His music frequently gets me fired up to go surf and work out! If you listen to his music, you’ll know Lecrae has been through a lot – growing up without his dad, struggling with drugs at one point, relationship problems, depression – he sings about it all. In our conversation, he shares how God brought him through – how God is all about RESTORATION and is still doing that work in his life each day. I hope this conversation brings you some light and encouragement! ✨

It feels soooooo good to be surfing! 🥲😃🥳 We just had a rad mini 1st surf trip after birthing my third son Micah! Great times with great people! 

It’s been hard to get in the water much and even the gym. So I’m just thankful for any fun I can get in the waves! Mama still got it 😆 I had low expectations and not much of a goal but just have some fun and enjoy surfing! 

Plus I was trying out some new boards & swapping out different fins & just experimenting with my new @rssurfco by @mgyenes_shapes 
So stoking on my boards, this board is my handcuffs!!! 
Fun times in Texas at @bsrsurfresort 🤙🏽

It may be hard to understand why some face so much pain and challenge in life. We may not always know the why or have the answer. But I believe that faith is trusting that Gods will is greater than our own.

node.text:
Have you tried turning off the noise and living life to the fullest?! 

What that looks like to me is something like this...

Living in my identity. Chasing my dreams passionately. Mindset adjustments. Letting go of comparison. Getting in the ocean and nature frequently. Acknowledging excuses and making shifts. Digital minimalism. Forgiving daily. Flipping fears. Living healthy so I have the energy to maximize each day. Enjoying and loving on my family. AND Most of all trusting in God with all that comes my way.

This world is no walk on the beach so we have got to equip ourselves to be resilient. 

You CAN live life to the fullest. #unstopabble

Check out my website for more motivation and tools to do the best version of you 🤙🏽❤️💯
